He, however, gets a bit of a tickle on it and the ball goes back to the keeper. Kyle Verreynne behind the stumps jumps to catch it but fails to pouch it. A single taken.
Back of a length, on off. Colin de Grandhomme blocks it out.
Good short ball by Marco Jansen! On middle from 'round the wicket. Colin de Grandhomme ducks under it.
A short ball, on off. Kyle Jamieson gets on top of the bounce and tickles it to fine leg for a single.
Slower through the air, on off. Colin de Grandhomme presses forwards and blocks it.
Flatter and quicker, on middle. Kyle Jamieson turns it to the leg side and takes a run.

Test match century number two for Colin de Grandhomme! What an innings this has been under pressure from this hard-hitting all-rounder! A counter-attacking knock this one and he has kept his team in the game with this innings. Shorter and outside off. Colin de Grandhomme cuts it past point and the batters run three as Colin de Grandhomme takes his helmet off and his team-mates as well as the crowd applauds him.
Quicker and flatter on middle. Colin de Grandhomme blocks it out.
On middle and fuller. Kyle Jamieson works it towards mid-wicket for a single. Bavuma misfields and allows a single.
Nicely bowled! Slower in the air on middle with a hint of turn. Kyle Jamieson defends it towards silly point.
Good-length delivery, outside off. Colin de Grandhomme leaves it alone for the keeper to collect.
Another short ball, outside off. Colin de Grandhomme does not offer any shot to that one and lets it sail through to the keeper.
Short of a length, outside off. Colin de Grandhomme sways away from the line of the ball.
Play and a miss! A bumper, outside off. Colin de Grandhomme looks to take it on but he fails to get any bat on it.
Another short ball, around off. Colin de Grandhomme ducks underneath.
A well-directed short ball, on middle. Kyle Jamieson tries to block but takes his eyes off the ball. The ball goes off the splice towards square leg for a run.
Fuller in length, outside off. Kyle Jamieson drives it wide of mid off and takes a single. He retains the strike.
A loopy ball, on a length, around off. Kyle Jamieson prods and keeps it out.
Slower through the air, on off. Kyle Jamieson defends it off the front foot.
Flatter and quicker, on middle. Kyle Jamieson hangs back and tucks it towards mid-wicket.
Tossed up, outside off. Colin de Grandhomme drives it to long off and takes a single.
Tosses it up, on off. Colin de Grandhomme gets forward to block.
Almost a similar delivery, short on middle. Kyle Jamieson again ducks under it comfortably.
Jansen goes 'round the wicket now and bangs this short angling into the batter. Kyle Jamieson ducks under it.
Back of a length, on off. Kyle Jamieson blocks it out comfortably.
Bangs this short on middle. Kyle Jamieson ducks under it.
On a length, on middle. Kyle Jamieson works it through mid-wicket for a couple.
Back of a length, on off. Kyle Jamieson blocks it solidly.
Marco Jansen (16-2-70-2) is back on.
Tossed up on middle. Colin de Grandhomme skips down the track and works it towards mid-wicket.
Quicker on middle and leg. Colin de Grandhomme blocks it out.
Fuller on middle. Kyle Jamieson pushes it to mid on and takes a single.
Fuller on middle this time. Colin de Grandhomme flicks it through mid-wicket this time and the batters run three. Good running.
Tossed up again around off. Colin de Grandhomme gets forward and defends it with soft hands.
Tossed up on off. Colin de Grandhomme blocks it out.

FOUR! This time he finds the gap! Back of a length, around off. Kyle Jamieson rides the bounce nicely again and punches it through covers for a boundary. The fielder dives near the fence to stop it but the ball races away towards the fence.
Tad shorter this time around off. Kyle Jamieson rides the bounce and punches it to covers.
Another length delivery on off. Kyle Jamieson blocks it solidly again.
Back of a length, on off. Kyle Jamieson blocks it out.
On a length, around off. Kyle Jamieson defends it towards the off side.
Short of a length, outside off. Colin de Grandhomme stays back and punches it to deep point for a single.
On a length, around off. Kyle Jamieson keeps it out.

In the air but just short of the silly point fielder! Tosses it up, on off. Kyle Jamieson gets forward and tries to block it with hard hands. The ball hits the splice and lands just in front of Dean Elgar at silly point.
This one goes on with the arm, from off. Kyle Jamieson keeps it out.
Quicker through the air, on middle. Kyle Jamieson stays back and blocks it.
Tosses it up, around off. Kyle Jamieson prods and defends it.
Flatter and quicker, around middle. Colin de Grandhomme hangs back and tucks it towards square leg for a run.
Shorter in length around off. Kyle Jamieson rides the bounce and defends it towards the off side.
On a length, on off. Kyle Jamieson blocks it out.
Back of a length, around off. Colin de Grandhomme pushes it to point for a single.
A good-length delivery, outside off. Colin de Grandhomme leaves it alone.

Ohh..beaten this time! Suddenly some tension out there. A good-length delivery around off. Colin de Grandhomme tries to push at it but the ball seams away a bit and beats the outside edge of his blade.
On a length, on off. Colin de Grandhomme blocks it out.

Daryl Mitchell though consults Colin de Grandhomme and takes the review. The replays roll in and the UltraEdge shows no bat involved. The Ball Tracker rolls and it shows three reds. So Daryl Mitchell has to walk back. Finally a wicket for South Africa!

Commentary.Commentary: Turn again, this time around off. Daryl Mitchell looks to defend but the ball catches the outside edge of his blade and falls short of the first slip.
Quicker again on off. Daryl Mitchell blocks it out.
Ohh..turn there for Maharaj! A flatter and quicker delivery on middle. Daryl Mitchell looks to block it but gets the outside half of his blade to covers.
A fullish delivery on off. Colin de Grandhomme leans forward and drives it to mid off.
Back of a length, on off. Colin de Grandhomme punches it to mid off.

Back of a length, on off at 129.8 kph. Daryl Mitchell blocks it solidly.
Back of a length, outside off. Daryl Mitchell gets across and defends it towards the off side.
A length delivery on off. Daryl Mitchell blocks it out.

Slightly shorter on middle. Colin de Grandhomme works it towards the leg side this time.

Tad fuller this time on off at 129.2 kph. Daryl Mitchell blocks it out.

DRINKS! Exactly the kind of start that New Zealand would have wished for on the moving day of this Test. The pair of Daryl Mitchell and Colin de Grandhomme has added 63 runs in the first hour without losing a wicket and they are ensuring that they stay in this contest. South Africa need to break this partnership sooner rather than later as these two batters can take the game away from them.

So a single to end the over! Tossed up nicely again on middle. Colin de Grandhomme works it to long leg this time for a single. Colin de Grandhomme looks more nervy and cautious against Keshav Maharaj but has managed to play him quite well so far.
Slower in the air again, on off. Colin de Grandhomme drives it to covers.
Tossed up this time on middle. Colin de Grandhomme gets forward and blocks it but gets the inside half of his blade to square leg.
Shorter on middle. Colin de Grandhomme works it towards mid-wicket.

Tad fuller this time on off. Daryl Mitchell drives it back to the bowler.
On a length, on off. Daryl Mitchell blocks it out off the front foot.
FOUR! Classy boundary but a poor delivery from Lutho Sipamla! He serves a full toss on leg. Daryl Mitchell just leans foward and creams this flick through mid-wicket for a boundary.
A full delivery on middle. Daryl Mitchell gets well forward and drives it to mid on.
A low full toss this time at 128.7, outside off. Colin de Grandhomme drives it to mid off for a single.
Starts with a fullish delivery on off. Colin de Grandhomme drives it to covers.

This time a bit slower in the air on middle. Daryl Mitchell gets well forward to defend it.
Flatter and quicker on middle. Daryl Mitchell takes a step or two forward and blocks it out.
On middle again. Colin de Grandhomme works it past mid-wicket this time for a single.
Quicker this time on middle and leg. Colin de Grandhomme gets back and nudges it just away from the short fine leg fielder.
Slightly slower on middle. Colin de Grandhomme works it towards mid-wicket again.
Darted on pads this time. Colin de Grandhomme works it to mid-wicket.
Fuller and on middle and leg. Colin de Grandhomme works it past square leg for a single.
A length delivery on off. Colin de Grandhomme defends this off the front foot to mid off.
Goes fuller again on off. Colin de Grandhomme drives it to mid on.
A fuller delivery on off. Colin de Grandhomme drives this off the inside half of his blade to mid-wicket.

FOUR! In the air...but safe and runs away for a boundary! A good short delivery on middle. Colin de Grandhomme pulls this but gets a top edge. The ball goes in the air but bisects the fine leg and square leg fielder for a boundary.
Back of a length, on off. Colin de Grandhomme gets back and blocks it.
Another loopy delivery on off with a hint of turn. Daryl Mitchell plants his front foot forward and blocks it.
Tossed up this time, around off. Daryl Mitchell pushes it towards the off side.
Fuller on middle now. Colin de Grandhomme drives it to long on for a single.
On middle and leg again. Colin de Grandhomme works it towards the leg side.
A flatter delivery on middle. Colin de Grandhomme works it to mid-wicket.

Another delivery that jags back in late from middle. Colin de Grandhomme tickles it towards fine leg and the batters take a run.
Back of a length, on middle and leg. Daryl Mitchell nudges it behind square on the leg side and collects a run.
A length ball, angling in late from off. Daryl Mitchell keeps it out.
BEATEN! Good-length delivery, around the corridor of uncertainty. Daryl Mitchell has a tentative poke at it but the ball beats his outside edge.
Short of a length, around middle. Colin de Grandhomme hangs back and just tucks it around the corner to rotate the strike.
On a length, around off. Colin de Grandhomme blocks it off the front foot.
Wiaan Mulder persists with full-length delivery, outside off. Daryl Mitchell drives it to the man at mid off. 9 runs off the over!
Fuller in length, outside off. Colin de Grandhomme drives but the fielder at cover dives to his left and keeps it to just one run.
A full ball, on off. Colin de Grandhomme drives it back to the bowler.
Back of a length, outside off. Colin de Grandhomme lets it be.
FOUR! Even better from Colin de Grandhomme! Another ball, full and this time, on middle. Colin de Grandhomme drives it back past the bowler and the ball races away to the long off fence.

On a length, around off. Daryl Mitchell blocks it out.

Good-length ball, angling in from outside off. Daryl Mitchell leaves it and the ball goes just past his off pole.
FOUR! Flicked away with aplomb! Daryl Mitchell brings up his FIFTY in style! A full ball, on middle. Mitchell flicks it through the mid-wicket region and the ball races away to the fence.
This is around middle and leg. Colin de Grandhomme flicks it behind square on the leg side and settles for a single.
Back of a length, on off. Colin de Grandhomme stays back to block but the ball hits the splice of his bat and pops out onto the deck.

A full ball, well outside off. Daryl Mitchell does not offer any shot to that one.
Good-length ball, on off. Daryl Mitchell defends it to the off side.
Full and outside off. Colin de Grandhomme drives it back past the bowler through mid off and comes back for the second run as the Rassie van der Dussen from mid on tracks it down.
On a length, angling in from outside off. Daryl Mitchell leaves it alone.
Back of a length, around off. Colin de Grandhomme stands tall and punches it through the cover region. The batters take three runs as the cover fielder cuts it off.
Fuller in length, around off. Daryl Mitchell defends it off the front foot.
A length ball, angling down leg. Daryl Mitchell misses his flick and the ball goes through to the keeper.
Short of a length, around off. Daryl Mitchell gets behind the line of the ball and blocks it.
Drags his length back and serves a good-length ball, on middle. Mitchell keeps it out.
A bit fuller this time, around off. Daryl Mitchell defends it to the off side.
Back of a length, outside off. Mitchell leaves it alone for the keeper to collect.
An overpitched ball, outside off. Daryl Mitchell drives it through covers. The fielder there gives it a chase and stops the ball just in front of the ropes. The batters take three runs.
Good-length delivery, outside off. Daryl Mitchell shoulders his arms to this one.
A length ball, angling in from middle. Colin de Grandhomme tickles it towards fine leg and collects a run.
A full ball, on middle. Daryl Mitchell flicks it wide of mid on and takes a single.

A length ball, nipping back in from off. Mitchell tries to block it off the front foot but it goes off the thick inside edge behind square on the leg side for a couple of runs.
Full and outside off. Colin de Grandhomme leans and drives but finds the fielder at wide mid off.

A full ball, outside off. Daryl Mitchell drives but Kagiso Rabada sticks his left hand out and stops the ball.
Another ball, on a length and around the fifth stump channel. Daryl Mitchell offers no shot to that one.
A length ball, outside off. Daryl Mitchell leaves it alone.
Short of a length, around off. Colin de Grandhomme sits back in his crease and defends it.
On a length, angling in from middle. Colin de Grandhomme flicks it behind square on the leg side and comes back for the second run.
Jansen goes short again, around off. Colin de Grandhomme lets it through to the keeper.
Good-length ball, jagging back in from off. Colin de Grandhomme lunges forward and blocks it solidly.

Jansen bends his back and serves a bumper, around off. Colin de Grandhomme ducks underneath.
Good-length delivery, angling in slightly from off. Daryl Mitchell keeps it out.
A full ball, outside off. Daryl Mitchell looks for a booming drive through covers but it goes off the inner half back to the bowler.
A length ball, on off. Daryl Mitchell blocks it out.
FOUR! Pulled away with disdain! Rabada serves a short ball, around off. Daryl Mitchell rocks back and pulls it in front of square on the leg side to bag a boundary.
On a length, around middle. Daryl Mitchell hangs back and defends it to the on side.
Rabada starts with a full ball, on middle. Daryl Mitchell clips it towards the mid-wicket fielder, along the ground.
Kagiso Rabada will start from the other end. Marco Jansen did not get much movement in the first over. Let's see what Rabada can do in his first over of the day. Here he comes...
Jansen bangs it into the deck, around off. Colin de Grandhomme ducks underneath.
Another ball, on a length and going on with the angle, from off. Colin de Grandhomme covers the line of the ball and tucks it to mid-wicket.
A short ball, angling in from outside off. Colin de Grandhomme lets it through to the keeper.
Fuller in length, outside off. Colin de Grandhomme mistimes his drive towards mid off.
Back of a length, outside off. Colin de Grandhomme has a poke at it but he misses.
FOUR! WOW! What a shot to start the day! A full ball, outside off. Colin de Grandhomme prods and carves it through covers for a boundary. New Zealand are underway on Day 3!

New Zealand under the pump in a home Test match! It is not often we have seen that in recent times. They have a tough task ahead of them today, especially in this first session with batting being the toughest in the morning session so far in this Test. It all depends on the pair of Daryl Mitchell and Colin de Grandhomme and out walk the players into the middle now. South African players are taking their respective field positions. Marco Jansen to start with the ball for South Africa and Colin de Grandhomme will be on strike to face the first ball of the day. Here we go...

With New Zealand still trailing by 207 runs, they need this partnership between Colin de Grandhomme and Daryl Mitchell to prosper further. They have the likes of Kyle Jamieson and Tim Southee to follow but it is really the partnership between these two that has to do the majority of the work from hereon. South Africa, are still in the driver’s seat and if they manage to break this partnership early in the day, it might just open the floodgates and we might see them taking a formidable lead here. The first session holds the key and if South Africa manage to win that session, it might get very difficult for the Kiwis to come back in this game. A very crucial first session of Day 3 coming up. Stay tuned.

Hello and a warm welcome to Day 3 of this second and final Test match between New Zealand and South Africa. South Africa have displayed their fighting spirit and have made a strong comeback in this Test after being demolished in the first Test match. The batting unit stepped up and managed to put a formidable total on the board and the bowling was excellent on Day 2 as they managed to send half of the Kiwi batting lineup back to the hut in a rather quick time. New Zealand, on the other hand, started promisingly on Day 2 with quick wickets but could not sustain the pressure and it was the late surge by Colin de Grandhomme with the bat and his partnership with Daryl Mitchell that has kept them in this game. It will be interesting to see how both teams go about their business on what is called as the moving day of the Test match.
... DAY 3, SESSION 1 …

Right then, South Africa have finally arrived in New Zealand. They were only physically present in the first Test but now they are physically, mentally and skillfully in New Zealand. The visitors are in the driver's seat and it's just a matter of breaking the current partnership. They still have a handy lead and one hour of disciplined bowling on the morning of Day 3 will further strengthen their chances in this Test match. For New Zealand, their hopes are pinned big time on Colin de Grandhomme and Daryl Mitchell. Another hour of Colin's blitz with the bat will be enough to bring this match in the balance. Plenty to look forward to on Sunday. Don't forget to join us. The first ball will be at 3.30 am IST (10 pm GMT, previous day) but as usual, our build-up will begin in advance. Until we meet again, it's goodbye and cheers!

Summarizing Day 2 - At the start of the day's play, South Africa had the advantage but that didn't last for long. The Kiwi bowlers turned up with full force and picked wickets at regular wickets. As many as four wickets went down in the morning session for just 60 runs and the hosts managed to restore some parity. Just when it appeared that the Proteas would get bundled out under 325, the pair of Marco Jansen and Keshav Maharaj joined forces. It was an assault from them on the strategy of Neil Wagner to bowl short as they took him to the cleaners and combined for a 62-run stand which catapulted South Africa's total above 350. Kagiso Rabada and Marco Jansen then made life tough for the Kiwi batters and hunted down 5 wickets together. The former, in particular, was very lethal in his spell after Tea and was too hot to handle.

An excellent second half of the final session for the Kiwis but in totality, the day has belonged to the touring party once more! The bowlers of South Africa put out a clinical show and decimated the top half of New Zealand's batting. They bowled according to the plan and got good support from the surface as well under overcast conditions (with the floodlights on). However, after the arrival of Colin de Grandhomme at the crease, things changed drastically. With the hosts reeling, Colin decided to throw caution to the wind and it paid off. His counter-punch stopped South Africa's charge and stole the momentum away a bit. Currently, he is involved in a 66-run stand with Daryl Mitchell and together, they have brought the deficit down to 207 runs.
Full and around middle, angling in, Daryl Mitchell brings down a straight bat and pushes it towards mid on. With that, it's time for STUMPS ON DAY 2!

Edgy! Pitches it up and around off, at 126 kph, Daryl Mitchell gets forward to defend but it gathers the inside edge and rolls to mid-wicket.
Goes very full with his length, around off at 125.9 kph, Daryl Mitchell drives it down to mid on.
Serves it on a length and around off, Daryl Mitchell is solidly behind the line as he blocks it to safety.
Last over of the day's play...
Quicker one, full and around leg, Colin pushes it down to mid on.

On middle, Daryl Mitchell turns it off his pads to mid-wicket for a single.
Fuller in length and on off, Daryl Mitchell drives it back to the bowler.

We're into overtime now. Still, 6 overs left in the day's play and the umpires can extend this session. In case you don't know, there was a break of around 15 minutes due to rain. Compensating for that!

Angling in, around middle, on a length. Daryl Mitchell blocks it out.
Good-length delivery, outside off. Daryl Mitchell leans and dabs it to point.
A yorker-length delivery, on middle. Daryl Mitchell digs it out.
A low full toss, on the pads. Daryl Mitchell flicks it towards deep mid-wicket for three runs. 150 up for New Zealand!
Fuller ball, around middle. Daryl Mitchell defends it out.
Slower through the air, very full, on middle, Daryl Mitchell knocks it to mid on.
Loopy ball, around middle and leg. Daryl Mitchell blocks it out solidly.
Tosses it up, around off. Daryl Mitchell leans to defend but gets an outside edge towards point.
Keshav Maharaj starts with a fuller ball, around middle. Daryl Mitchell steps down and pushes it to mid-wicket.
It's time for some spin! Keshav Maharaj is introduced into the attack. Let's see how Colin de Grandhomme responds to this challenge.
Much fuller now, around middle, Colin de Grandhomme shows the full face of the bat and pushes it towards mid on.
That's a beauty! Lutho Sipamla feeds it on a length close to off, Colin de Grandhomme tries to play the line but it nips away to beat the bat.
Tad shorter, outside off. Colin de Grandhomme leaves it alone.
More runs! A fuller ball, outside off. Colin de Grandhomme drives it past cover for a brace. 50 for Colin de Grandhomme off just 36 balls! What an innings this has been!
FOUR! Colin de Grandhomme is making it look so easy here! Another beautiful shot! Touch shorter, width on offer. Colin de Grandhomme waits for it and cuts it past point for a boundary.
Length, around middle, Colin de Grandhomme blocks it out.
Back of a length, around middle and leg, Daryl Mitchell taps it towards square leg off his toes.
Good-length delivery, around middle. Daryl Mitchell defends it out.
On a length, outside off. Colin de Grandhomme cuts it past point for a single. That brings up the 50-run stand between these two! Much needed partnership for New Zealand!

FOUR! Edgy runs! A full toss, outside off. Colin de Grandhomme looks to drive but the ball goes off the outside edge past gully for a boundary. Marco Jansen has overstepped here and a no ball is called!
Another short ball, around middle, Colin de Grandhomme once again ducks underneath it.
Marco Jansen drops it short now, around middle. Colin de Grandhomme ducks and lets that go through.
Good-length delivery, outside off, at 133.3 clicks. Daryl Mitchell presses forward and taps it towards point for a quick single.
Good-length delivery, outside off, at 127.9 clicks. Colin de Grandhomme leaves it alone. 10 runs off the over!
A low full toss, on middle. Colin de Grandhomme works it away towards mid on.
Back of a length, outside off. Colin de Grandhomme cuts it to the fielder at point.
SIX! Colin de Grandhomme is in the mood to thrill! He is scoring runs freely now! A shorter ball, around middle, Colin de Grandhomme gets under that and pulls it over wide long on for a biggie.
FOUR! Lovely shot! Back of a length, outside off. Colin de Grandhomme stays in his crease and slashes this past point for a boundary.
Lutho Sipamla goes over the wicket, delivers a fuller ball, around off. Colin de Grandhomme drives from the toe end of his bat towards mid off.
Lutho Sipamla comes back into the attack. 0/16 in his 5 overs so far.
On a length, around middle. Daryl Mitchell blocks it out.
Change in angle for Marco Jansen. He goes 'round the wicket, serves a length ball, around middle. Daryl Mitchell blocks it out.
Angling in, around middle and leg, on a length. Colin de Grandhomme taps it towards mid-wicket and takes another single.
Much fuller now, outside off. Daryl Mitchell drives it wide of mid off and rotates the strike!
Back of a length, down the leg side. Colin de Grandhomme tucks it towards mid-wicket for a single.
Marco Jansen serves it on a length, on middle. Colin de Grandhomme defends it out.
Marco Jansen is back on. 10-2-38-2 are his figures so far.
On a length, around middle. Colin de Grandhomme looks to push this but gets an inside edge towards square leg, for a single.
Tad fuller, darting it on the pads. Daryl Mitchell flicks it towards square leg for a single.
Shorter ball now, around middle. Daryl Mitchell stays in his crease and defends it out.
Good-length delivery, outside off. Daryl Mitchell blocks it out.
Outside off now, on a length. Daryl Mitchell dabs it towards point.
Angling in, on a length, around middle and leg. Daryl Mitchell taps it towards square leg.
Back of a length, outside off. Colin de Grandhomme shoulders his arms at it. A dull dot to end the over.
FOUR! That's crunched through the off side, Colin de Grandhomme is putting on a show and is looking in the mood. Short in length and wide outside off, Colin camps back and smacks it through point.
FOUR! 10 off 2 balls now!  On a length, around the pads. Colin de Grandhomme heaves it towards deep square leg for a boundary.

SIX! High and handsome! Boundaries are big here, not big enough for Colin de Grandhomme! A shorter ball, around middle, Colin de Grandhomme gets under it and pulls it towards deep square leg for a biggie!
Angling in, around middle and leg, on a length. Colin de Grandhomme blocks it out.
Touch shorter, outside off. Colin de Grandhomme leaves it alone.
EDGED...but just short! On a length, outside off. Daryl Mitchell looks to block this, but the ball goes off the outside edge and falls just short of Dean Elgar at first slip.
Back of a length, on middle. Daryl Mitchell defends it out.
On a length, around off. Colin de Grandhomme looks to push this away but gets an inside edge towards fine leg for a single.
FOUR! Wonderful shot! Much fuller now, outside off. Colin de Grandhomme leans and drives it beautifully past covers for a boundary.
Good-length delivery, outside off. Colin de Grandhomme leaves it alone.
Leg bye! On a length, darting it on the thigh pad. Daryl Mitchell looks to flick but misses. The ball deflects off his thigh pad and goes towards fine leg. A leg bye is taken!
Angling in on a length outside off and then straightening off the surface, once again Colin offers no shot.
Bowls it on a good length and outside off, de Grandhomme is not interested in playing at that.
Inviting delivery. On a length and outside off, Colin de Grandhomme shoulders arms.
On a length and outside off, Mitchell taps it down to extra cover for a run. 100 up for New Zealand for the loss of five wickets.
Full and on middle, Daryl flicks it across the line but Rassie van der Dussen makes a good stop at mid-wicket.
Full and close to off, angling in, Daryl Mitchell brings his bat ahead of the front pad in defense.
In the channel outside off, Colin lets it be.
This one is angled in, around off, Colin de Grandhomme stays on the back foot and defends it to the leg side.
Hurls across a length ball outside off, Colin offers no shot.
Around off, on a length, defended from the crease.
FOUR! Full in length and outside off, driven firmly through covers for a boundary.
The batter shoulders arms to let that one through.
Bowls it on a length and outside off, shaping away, Daryl Mitchell has an easy leave on this occasion. End of a probing over!
Again it's on a length and around off, this time DM covers the line better and defends it from the middle of his bat.
Identical to the last delivery, once again Mitchell stays back to play the line but gets beaten by the slight away movement.
Beaten all ends up! It's all happening here. Mulder serves it on a length around off, it angles in and then leaves the batter, Daryl Mitchell squared up in defense and it goes past the outside edge.
Another delivery on a good length outside off, holding its line, Daryl Mitchell offers no shot.
Lands it on a length outside off, shaping away, Daryl allows it through to the keeper.
Spears in a very full ball on middle, Mitchell knocks it down in the gap at mid-wicket for a single.
Delivers it on a good length and around off, shaping in, Mitchell shoulders arms.
Fuller in length and outside off, Colin de Grandhomme drives it through covers for three runs.

DRINKS! South Africa have been all over New Zealand. They have bowled exceptionally well and have managed to send half their side back to the hut. The hosts are in all sorts of trouble here, they need a partnership to try and rebuild the innings. Colin de Grandhomme joins Daryl Mitchell out in the middle.

OUT! LEFT ALONE AND BOWLED! New Zealand are in a world of trouble now. This is excellent bowling from Kagiso Rabada. Delivers it on a fuller length around off, at 133.2 kph. The ball lands and jags back in off the seam. Tom Blundell takes his front leg forward a wee bit, doesn't expect the ball to move back in so much and hence he shoulders arms. To his surprise, the ball has naughtily seamed back in off the surface and gone on to shatter the stumps. Big misjudgement on his part. New Zealand trail by 273 runs and have lost half their side.
Commentary.Howout: b Kagiso Rabada

Commentary.Commentary: FOUR! Aerial but through the gap. Rabada won't mind that shot. Fuller in length and outside off, Tom Blundell reaches out for it and crunches it through covers for a boundary.
Back of a length, around off, Blundell goes on his toes in defense.
Kagiso Rabada (8-2-18-2) comes back into the attack.
Beaten! Wiaan Mulder serves it full and around off, angling in and then holding its line, Mitchell is beaten on the drive.
Serves it on a length and outside off, Daryl covers his stumps and allows it through.
Fuller and on off, Mitchell drives it down towards mid on.
Around off, on a length, defended off the back foot.
Fuller and outside off, Blundell drives it towards cover for a single.
Outside off, left alone.
On the pads, whipped wide of short leg for a couple of runs.
The batter has just blocked that from his crease.
Bouncer, around middle and off, ducked.
Back of a length, around middle, Tom Blundell defends it down in front of short leg. The ball sneaks past him and he gets off the mark with a single.
Tom Blundell comes to the crease now.

OUT! CAUGHT! That's a trap by Dean Elgar and Henry Nicholls falls for it. There is a fielder placed at an unusual position, you can call it a deepish backward point that is halfway from the boundary. Short in length and outside off, Henry Nicholls finds it in his range and whacks it through the line. This is more of an instinctive shot from him as he favours that side of the field. Not sure whether he was aware of that fielder or not. His shot doesn't have the elevation to clear the fielder and Sarel Erwee takes a simple catch. A body blow to the Kiwis! It was a plan and the South African players are ecstatic, especially Keshav Maharaj. Was he the one to come up with this strategy?
Commentary.Howout: c Sarel Erwee b Marco Jansen

Commentary.Commentary: FOUR! Pure timing! Fuller and on middle, Henry Nicholls picks it off his pads and flicks it supremely through wide mid on for a boundary.
Fuller and on middle, Darly drives it down the ground but finds mid on.
Delivers it outside off, Mitchell allows it through.

HUGE SHOUT FOR AN LBW! Once again the finger stays down. Dean Elgar is hesitant but eventually goes for the DRS. Missing the stumps, confirms the Ball Tracking. South Africa lose a review, they are now down to one. It was yet another inswinger from Mulder, struck Mitchell high on the pads.
Another delivery in the channel outside off, it's not entertained by the batter.
In the zone outside off, Daryl offers no shot.

Howwzzaat? Mulder gets a length ball to nip back in from around off, Mitchell fails to defend from the crease and is hit on the front pad. They appeal but the umpire shakes his head. Height seems to be a factor now. Dean Elgar reviews but the Ball Tracking shows that it's clipping the top of the leg stump. Umpire's call. South Africa don't lose the review.
Outside off, on a good length, Nicholls leaves.
The batter has just blocked that from his crease.
Jansen returns to bowling it on a length, outside off, it's allowed through to the keeper.
FOUR! Sublime! A juicy half-volley outside off, Henry Nicholls leans into the drive, transfers his weight beautifully into the shot and creams it through covers for a glorious boundary.
Around off, on a length, defended from the back foot.
Pitches it up and around off, Nicholls leans forward to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
In the channel outside off, DM has nothing to do with it. End of an eventful first over by Wiaan Mulder!

EDGY FOUR! Mulder induces an outside edge. Hurls across a length delivery, around off and it bounces a tad extra. Mitchell is squared up in defense and edges it past the diving second slip fielder for a boundary.
A bit short and wide outside off, Daryl shoulders arms.
The batter has just blocked that from his crease.
Lands it on a length and close to off, Mitchell defends it watchfully.
In the zone outside off, on a length, it's left alone.

FOUR! That's dispatched! Mulder serves a short ball around off at 133 kph, Daryl Mitchell rides the bounce and pulls it with authority to the deep square leg fence. It's called a no ball as well for overstepping.
Wiaan Mulder comes into the attack now.
Good length. This one is on a length and just outside off, keeping its line, Henry Nicholls shoulders arms.
Pitches it up and outside off, Henry drives it delightfully through the line. Maharaj dives at covers and takes the pace off the ball. Saves two runs for his team.
Around off, on a length, it's defended watchfully by Henry Nicholls.
Extra bounce and movement. It lands on a length around off, Nicholls fails to defend and is hit high on the thigh pad.
Angling in from a length around off, Henry defends it from the back foot.
Serves it full and outside off, Nicholls brings out the square drive but finds the fielder.
On a length, around middle and leg. Daryl Mitchell defends it out.
FOUR! Classy! Another fuller ball, around off. Daryl Mitchell presents the full face of the bat and drives it past mid off for a boundary. The deficit is now 300!
FOUR! Nicely done! Much fuller now, around middle and leg. Daryl Mitchell flicks it uppishly past the fielder at mid-wicket for a boundary.
Another length ball, angling in, around middle, Daryl Mitchell pushes it towards mid on.
On a length, around middle, Daryl Mitchell blocks it out.
Pitches it up, outside off. Daryl Mitchell defends it out.
Back of a length, outside off. Henry Nicholls taps it towards point. End of a successful over for Jansen.
FOUR! Put away! Shorter ball, outside off. Henry Nicholls stays in his crease and punches it past point for a boundary.
In the region outside off, left alone by Henry.
Short and around off, Mitchell stands tall and pushes it away at covers for a brisk run.
Daryl Mitchell is the new batter at number 5. New Zealand trail by 313 runs.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! This is exactly the way Tom Latham got dismissed. South Africa have managed to break this partnership and they have got their third. A fuller ball, down the leg side at 138.6 kph. Devon Conway looks to flick but manages a fine tickle behind to the keeper. Kyle Verreynne dives to his right and takes another good catch. Marco Jansen strikes and gets rid of Devon Conway. The home team is in big trouble now!
Commentary.Howout: c Kyle Verreynne b Marco Jansen

Commentary.Commentary: FOUR! Top shot! That sounded so sweet as soon as it left the bat! A shorter ball, around middle, Devon Conway pulls it through square leg for a cracking boundary.
Devon Conway is not ready and pulls out. Marco Jansen will have to reload.
On a length, outside off. Henry Nicholls blocks it out solidly.
Lutho Sipamla delivers it on a fuller length, outside off. Henry Nicholls drives but finds mid off.
Fuller ball, outside off, at 127.4 kph. Henry Nicholls presses forward and drives it straight to the fielder at cover.
Tad fuller, around off, at 132.7 clicks. Henry Nicholls leans and defends it out.
This one lands on a length, outside off, swinging away. Henry Nicholls leaves it alone.
Full in length, outside off, shaping away. Henry Nicholls opens the face of his bat and pushes it past point for a couple of runs.
Spraying it down the leg side, fuller in length. Devon Conway misses his flick.
Fuller now, angling in, around off. Devon Conway defends it out.
Good-length delivery, outside off. Devon Conway blocks it out.
Lenght ball, around middle, extra bounce there again! Devon Conway looks to tuck this away, but the ball hits him on his gloves and stays on the leg side.
Length ball, outside off. It shoots off the surface and Conway defends it with a loose bottom hand near the popping crease.
Marco Jansen serves a full ball, darting it on the pads. Devon Conway clips it towards deep mid-wicket for a brace.
Marco Jansen returns for his second spell. 5-2-14-0 are his figures so far. Two slips and a gully in place...
Good-length delivery, outside off, shaping away at 130.5 clicks. Henry Nicholls leaves it alone. Maiden over!
Lutho Sipamla delivers it on a length, way wide of off, shaping away further. Henry Nicholls does not fiddle with it.
Swinging away, outside off, on a length. Henry Nicholls watches it sail through to the keeper.
Lutho Sipamla delivers it on a length, outside off. Henry Nicholls taps it towards point.
Full again, outside off. Henry Nicholls leans and defends it out.
Fuller ball, outside off. Henry Nicholls leaves it alone.
Shortish and on off, Henry stands back and drops it with gentle hands to covers. Takes a single.
Around off, on a length, the batter has just watchfully blocked this out.

DROPPED! Oh, dear! A tough chance goes down! A fuller ball, around middle and off, Devon Conway drives it back uppishly, to the left of the bowler. Kagiso Rabada tries to grab with his left hand in his follow-through but fails to do so. The ball rolls behind and they collect a single.
Shorter ball, around off. Henry Nicholls stands tall and punches it towards covers for a single.
FOUR! Edgy runs! On a length, outside off. Henry Nicholls stays in his crease and looks to block this, but the ball goes off the outside edge past the slip cordon for a boundary.
Back of a length, angling down the leg side, Henry allows it through to the keeper.
Serves a length ball, outside off. Devon Conway leaves it alone.

A shout for LBW, but the umpire says no! Another length ball, nipping back in, from around middle and leg. Devon Conway shuffles across and looks to clip this away but misses and gets hit on his front pad. The replay shows the ball was just clipping the leg pole.
Back of a length, outside off. Devon Conway lets that go through to the keeper.
FOUR! Easy pickings! Much fuller now, around middle and leg. Devon Conway flicks it past mid-wicket for a boundary.

TWO WIDES! Good-length delivery, swinging away, wide of off. Henry Nicholls lets that go through. Kyle Verreynne dives to his left, to grab the ball but fails. The ball deflects off his gloves and goes third man. Wide called and a run is taken as well!
Another length ball, swinging away, outside off. Henry Nicholls leaves it alone.
On a length, outside off, shaping away. Henry Nicholls offers no shot!
Good-length delivery, around middle and leg. Devon Conway tucks it towards square leg. Excellent over from Kagiso Rabada!

Play and a miss! This is exceptional bowling from Kagiso Rabada. He is making the ball talk both ways. This time it's an outswinger. Landing close to off, on a length and leaving the batter with the seam movement. Conway pushes at it tamely and misses.

SHOUT FOR A CAUGHT BEHIND! Rabada gets a length ball to nip back in from a length around off, Conway tries to defend by getting forward but it sneaks past the inside edge. It goes behind to the keeper and there is some noise. They appeal but the umpire shakes his head. South Africa decide not to review. The replays, later on, show that it had clipped the thigh pad of Devon's back leg.

APPEAL FOR AN LBW! Not given. On a length again, nipping back in, around middle, Devon Conway looks to flick but misses and gets rapped on the pads again. A huge shout for an lbw! It's not given. Dean Elgar has a word with his bowler and then takes the DRS. No bat is involved, shows the UltraEdge. The Ball Tracking indicates that it's going over the stumps. Devon Conway survives, and South Africa lose a review here!
This one nips back in, on a length, around middle, Devon Conway looks to flick but misses and gets hit on the thigh pad.
Good-length delivery, on middle. Devon Conway taps it towards point.
The artificial lights are switched back on. Kagiso Rabada to continue from this end.
Length, outside off. Henry Nicholls shoulders his arms at it. A maiden for Lutho Sipamla!
Much fuller on this occasion, shaping away, wide of off, at 129.3 clicks. Henry Nicholls offers no shot.
This one lands on a length, outside off. Henry Nicholls lets that go through to the keeper.
Good-length delivery now, shaping away, outside off. Henry Nicholls leaves it alone.
Another full delivery, outside off. Henry Nicholls presses forward and drives it towards cover.
Lutho Sipamla starts off with a fuller ball, around off. Henry Nicholls leans and blocks it out.

We are back for the final session of the day! The players are out in the middle. Devon Conway and Henry Nicholls will resume their batting. Lutho Sipamla will begin with the ball. 34 overs left. Here we go...
... DAY 2, SESSION 3 ...
... DAY 2, SESSION 3 ...

A window of 11 overs before Tea and South Africa put their best foot forward. Kagiso Rabada removed both the Kiwi openers cheaply and for the first time on this tour, the Proteas are on top. Devon Conway and Henry Nicholls weathered the storm but have not looked convincing. They have a big task ahead of them after this break. The main highlight of the afternoon session though has to be the counter-attacking partnership between Marco Jansen and Keshav Maharaj where they attacked the Kiwi bowlers, especially Neil Wagner and took South Africa's total past the 350-run mark. The touring team would now aim to pick as many wickets as possible in the evening and keep the advantage in their corner. Do join us in a short while for more action.
Another length ball, outside off. Devon Conway lets that go through. That will be Tea on Day 2!
Angling in, on a length, outside off. Devon Conway lets that go through.
Length ball now, outside off. Devon Conway offers no shot.
Kagiso Rabada drops it short now, around middle and leg. Devon Conway leaves it alone.
Fuller now, outside off. Devon Conway leaves it alone.
Fuller ball, outside off. Devon Conway lunges forward and pushes it towards cover.
Shaping away, on a length and outside off, Nicholls has nothing to do with it.
Angling in from around off, on a length, Nicholls defends it towards the leg side.
FOUR! Poor delivery and punished! Short in length wide outside off, Henry Nicholls latches onto the width and slaps it past the right side of the backward point fielder for a boundary.
On a good length outside off, left alone.
That is left alone for the keeper to collect.
Fuller in length and around off, Nicholls defends it off his front foot to covers.
In the zone outside off, left alone.

UPPISH AND IT'S FOUR! Rabada hurries up the batter with a sharp short ball around off, Conway pulls it compulsively and hits it in the air towards deep backward square leg off the top edge. Lutho Sipamla rushes across to his right from fine leg but it drops safely away from him. The ball lands and spins as Sipamla overruns. It goes behind him and crosses the fence. Elgar smiles.
In the channel outside off, angling in, Conway lets it be.
Full and wide outside off, left alone.

On a good length around off, shaping in, Conway gets across and closes the face of his bat. It takes the inner portion and rolls behind square leg. Rassie van der Dussen there makes a half stop and prevents a single.
Angles in a length ball around off, some extra bounce, Conway fails to flick and is hit high on the back leg.
Change of bat for Devon Conway.
Angles in a length ball around off, Henry stays back to guard his stumps and shoulders arms.
Outside off, left alone.

FOUR! That's aerial and just away from the point fielder. Short in length, wide outside off, Henry cracks it off his back foot towards point. The fielder there, Sarel Erwee, stretches his hands to his left but it goes whiskers away from him and scoots behind for a boundary.

FOUR! Very efficient! Marco Jansen gets greedy, attempts to bowl an outswinger from middle and leg. He lands it full at 138.9 kph, Henry Nicholls flicks it through mid-wicket and it races away to the fence, beating the effort of Lutho Sipamla near the fence.
Identical to the last delivery, this time Henry allows it through to the keeper.
Beaten! Loose from Nicholls. A touch short in length outside off, Henry Nicholls goes back to punch it through the line but it nips away a shade to beat the outside edge.
On a good length and outside off, angling in, Conway covers his stumps and lets it through to the keeper.
Serves it just ahead of a length around off, Conway lunges and defends it with an angled bat to gully.
Back of a length, wide outside off, Henry goes back and steers it in the gap at covers for a single.
Hurls it on a good length and outside off, getting it to straighten off the seam, Nicholls shoulders arms.
Slightly short and on off, again Nicholls goes on the back foot and blocks it down safely.
Change of angle from Rabada. He speeds in from 'round the wicket and darts in a length ball on off, Nicholls defends it off his back foot.
That's a beauty! Marco Jansen delivers it on a good length and close to off, it lands and swings away, Conway tries to push inside the line and misses. Maiden!
In the channel outside off, moving away off the seam, Devon is watchful as he allows it through.
Gets close to off this time, on a length, Conway gently defends it with an angled bat to the off side.
Again the line is too wide outside off to bother the batter. Conway is at ease in leaving those.
Lands it on a length outside off, shaping away again, Conway leans forward and then leaves.
A touch short in length and outside off, shaping away, Conway has nothing to do with it.
Short again, around middle. Henry Nicholls ducks and lets that go through. End of a successful over!
Short again, outside off this time. Henry Nicholls shows the full face of his bat and blocks it out solidly.
Tad shorter now, around middle, Henry Nicholls stays in his crease and defends it out.
FOUR! Henry Nicholls gets off the mark in style! A fuller delivery now, around middle and leg. Henry Nicholls uses his wrists and flicks it past mid-wicket for a boundary.
Back of a length, around middle. Henry Nicholls stays in his crease and taps it away from the fielder at short leg.
Henry Nicholls, the centurion of the last Test match, walks in next at number 4.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Kagiso Rabada has two and it's a fantastic start for South Africa. Both the Kiwi openers are back in the hut now. This one is served on a good length outside off, some extra bounce there as it holds its line after landing. Will Young has a needless poke inside the line as he hangs his bat out to dry and edges it behind. Kyle Verreynne gets into the act again and this time it's a straightforward catch for him. New Zealand are in an early spot of bother.
Commentary.Howout: c Kyle Verreynne b Kagiso Rabada

Commentary.Commentary: Tad fuller, down the leg side. Will Young glances it towards fine leg for a single.
Length ball, around middle. Will Young defends it out.

Half an appeal for LBW, but turned down! A length ball, nipping in, around middle and leg. Devon Conway walks across and looks to flick but misses. The ball deflects off his pads and goes towards fine leg. Leg bye taken! That was close, but South Africa did not seem interested in that. The Ball Tracking shows that it was clipping the leg stump.
On a length again, around middle. Devon Conway blocks it out.
Length ball, around middle and leg. Devon Conway looks to flick but gets an inside edge onto his thigh pad.
Back of a length, around middle, Will Young taps it towards mid-wicket for a single.
Another length ball, nipping away, outside off, at 135.5 clicks. Devon Conway leaves it alone.
Good-length delivery, outside off. Devon Conway offers no shot.
On a length, around middle. Devon Conway leans and defends it out solidly.
Fuller now, around middle and leg. Will Young flicks it past square leg for a single. He opens his account.
Another length ball, drifting away, outside off at 138 clicks. Will Young offers no shot.
On a length, outside off. Will Young shoulders his arms at it.
Outside off, another outswinger, touch shorter. Devon Conway lets that go through.
This one lands on a shorter length, shaping away, outside off, at 134.9 clicks. Devon Conway pushes it towards gully.
Back of a length, around off. Devon Conway blocks it out off the back foot.
The umpire is keeping a close eye on Marco Jansen's landing.
Tad shorter. around middle. Devon Conway defends it out.
Length ball, shaping away again, around off. Devon Conway taps it on the off side.
Marco Jansen begins with a shorter ball, shaping away outside off. Devon Conway leaves it alone
Marco Jansen to share the new cherry from the other end.
Fuller now, outside off, at 137.1 clicks. Will Young blocks it out. Successful first over for South Africa!
Length ball, down the leg side. Devon Conway flicks it past Rassie van der Dussen at short leg for a single. He gets off the mark!
Devon Conway walks in next.

OUT! Strangled down the leg side and it's a big breakthrough for South Africa! Rabada serves a length ball down the leg side, at 132 kph, Latham tries to flick it off his pads but all he manages is a fine tickle behind. Kyle Verreynne dives full length to his right and takes a fantastic catch. Tom turns and returns, without even waiting for the finger to go up. Early setback for the Kiwis.
Commentary.Howout: c Kyle Verreynne b Kagiso Rabada

Commentary.Commentary: Oh, dear! A length ball, around middle and leg. Tom Latham flicks this towards short leg. Rassie van der Dussen is stationed there who is late to react and is pinged on the helmet.
FOUR LEG BYES! On a length, around leg. Tom Latham misses his flick and the ball deflects off his thigh pad and rolls towards fine leg for a boundary. New Zealand are underway!
Kagiso Rabada beings with a length ball, around middle and leg. Tom Latham looks to flick this but misses and gets hit on the pads.

We are back for the final session of Day 4! The final innings of this Test match is set to get underway. South African players are out there in the middle. The two openers for New Zealand, Tom Latham and Will Young are out there as well to start their chase. Kagiso Rabada will start with the ball for South Africa and he will be on a hat-trick as he got last two wickets of consecutive deliveries in first innings. Here we go...
... DAY 4, SESSION 3 …

Right then! New Zealand need a mammoth 426 runs to win the Test as well as the series! They have their task cut out as they face a formidable South African bowling attack. It promises to be an intriguing last session on Day 4, so stay tuned as the live action begins shortly.

New Zealand bowled well in patches but they were well below-par on Day 4. They lost the plot when the South African batters started attacking them and that could also cost them the match. Every bowler got into the wickets column but one would think that they clearly missed the trick of playing a spinner on this track.

South Africa didn't start off well with the bat but there were a couple of partnerships that swung the momentum back in their favour - Temba Bavuma and Rassie van der Dussen, Wiaan Mulder and Kyle Verreynne. But the partnership which New Zealand didn't enjoy at all was the one between Kagiso Rabada and Kyle Verreynne. That passage of play completely shifted the momentum in South Africa's favour and the last wicket partnership dented New Zealand's hopes further.

A terrific batting performance from South Africa and they are in a very commanding position now. Kyle Verreynne has been brilliant with the bat for them and there have been some important contributions around him that has ensured that they set a huge target for the Kiwis. They have declared their innings just few minutes before Tea, as a result, early Tea has been taken.

Here we go... South Africa declare now! A short delivery on middle. Lutho Sipamla pulls it to fine leg for a single. This has been a very good batting performance by South Africa. South Africa declare weith 354/9 in their second innings. New Zealand need 426 runs to win this Test match!
Another short delivery on middle. Lutho Sipamla ducks under it now. Not sure why South Africa are not declaring!
A short delivery on middle this time. Lutho Sipamla looks to pull but misses.
A full delivery on off. Kyle Verreynne digs it out to mid off for a single.
A yorker-length ball, on middle. Kyle Verreynne digs it out back to the bowler.
A slower ball, full and around leg. Kyle Verreynne clips it towards deep mid-wicket and comes back for the second run.
A full ball, outside off. Lutho Sipamla drags it towards mid on.
Another short ball, around off. Lutho Sipamla tries to pull but it hits his forearm and then ricochets onto the helmet.

Lutho Sipamla has been hit on the helmet here as he tried to pull that ball! The physio comes out for the mandatory concussion test and this will take more time out of the game. All the cameras are on Dean Elgar now and we might see the declaration any time soon. In the meanwhile, Lutho Sipamla looks fine and is ready to resume.
NASTY! A bumper, around off. Lutho Sipamla misses his pull and gets struck on his helmet.
A length ball, around middle. Lutho Sipamla tucks it to mid-wicket.
A slower ball, full and around off. Lutho Sipamla digs it out.
Full and outside off. Kyle Verreynne drags it to deep point and manages only a single in the end.
A short ball to end the over, down leg. Lutho Sipamla lets it sail through to the keeper.
Wagner goes full, outside off. Lutho Sipamla drives but finds the cover fielder.
A short ball, on middle. Lutho Sipamla ducks underneath watchfully.
On a length, outside off. Kyle Verreynne cuts it to deep point and takes a single.
Play and a miss! A slower ball, into the wicket, on middle. Kyle Verreynne shimmies down the track and looks to heave it away but he mises.
A slower ball, around leg. Kyle Verreynne steps out to flick but he misses.
Neil Wagner is back on. He replaces Kyle Jamieson.
Another ball, short of a length, on off. Lutho Sipamla blocks it out.
Good-length delivery, on off. Lutho Sipamla hangs back and punches it down to mid off.
Short and wide, outside off. Kyle Verreynne cuts it to deep point and settles for a single.
Back of a length, around off. Kyle Verreynne defends it off the back foot.

A misfield and they get the run in the end. Good-length ball, around off. Lutho Sipamla stays back to block but it goes off the outer half of the bat towards the gully region where the fielder fumbles and the batters take a single.
A full ball, outside off. Kyle Verreynne drills it to long off for a run.
Back of a length, around off. Lutho Sipamla blocks it out.
A short ball, outside off. Lutho Sipamla ducks underneath.
On a length, around off. Lutho Sipamla keeps it out.

FOUR! Cries of catch it but the ball goes over the keeper. Banged into the surface, around middle. Lutho Sipamla gets cramped and he looks to block. It goes the glove and flies over the keeper's head for a boundary.
Banged into the deck, on middle. Kyle Verreynne pulls it along the ground towards deep square leg for a run.
FOUR! Nicely done! Back of a length, on middle and leg. Kyle Verreynne swivels and pulls it behind square on the leg side for a boundary.
Wide! Too short, outside off. Kyle Verreynne lets it be and the umpire calls it wide for height.
Short delivery this time on middle. Lutho Sipamla ducks under it.
Back of a length, on off. Lutho Sipamla blocks it out.
On a length, on off. Lutho Sipamla blocks it out.
A fuller delivery on middle. Kyle Verreynne drives it to mid on for a single.
DROPPED! Kyle Jamieson drops a sitter now! A short delivery around leg. Lutho Sipamla pulls it straight to Kyle Jamieson at fine leg but he drops it. A single taken.
On a length, around off. Lutho Sipamla pushes it towards the off side.

DRINKS! South Africa are well ahead in this game now and it is just a matter of time before they either declare or get bowled out by the opposition. New Zealand have leaked a lot of runs in the last few overs and they need to get the last wicket quickly if they are to have any chances of chasing down the target in the fourth innings.
A full toss, outside off. Kyle Verreynne toe-ends this slap towards the off side.
A length delivery, again very wide outside off. Kyle Verreynne lets it go again but the umpire does not call it wide this time.
WIDE! Full and very wide outside off. Kyle Verreynne leaves it alone and the umpire calls it wide.
Back of a length, on middle. Kyle Verreynne defends it again.
A length ball, on off. Kyle Verreynne blocks it out.
A full delivery, on off. Kyle Verreynne drives it to deep cover and denies a single.
A full delivery, outside off. Kyle Verreynne leaves this one alone.
A very full delivery on off. Lutho Sipamla blocks it out.
A full delivery on middle. Lutho Sipamla flicks it through mid-wicket for a couple.
Southee bangs this short on middle and leg. Lutho Sipamla ducks under it.
Short and wide outside off. Kyle Verreynne cuts it to deepish point for a single now.
Back of a length, around off. Lutho Sipamla punches it to point and takes a single. The lead is now 400!
On a length, on off. Lutho Sipamla blocks it out.
SIX! What a shot this is! Short and around off. Kyle Verreynne backs away and slaps it over point for a maximum.
Lutho Sipamla is the last man in.

OUT! TAKEN! Keshav Maharaj departs now in a bid to get more quick runs! Kyle Jamieson bangs this short again on middle. Maharaj looks to pull but is hurried on this pull shot. He gets the top edge and the ball goes towards mid-wicket and Colin de Grandhomme runs behind to take a good catch. So nine down but the damage has been done.
Commentary.Howout: c Colin de Grandhomme b Kyle Jamieson

Commentary.Commentary: On a length, around off. Kyle Verreynne dabs it towards point and takes a risky single.
FOUR! Three in a row now! Back of  a length, outside off. Kyle Verreynne slaps it towards deep exra-cover for a boundary.
FOUR! Another short ball and another boundary! Kyle Jamieson bangs it short on middle. Kyle Verreynne pulls it firmly towards deep square leg for a boundary.
FOUR! He is now taking on the bowling. A short delivery outside off. Kyle Verreynne pulls it towards long on. The ball goes high in the air towards long on, one bounce into the fence.
On a length, on off. Keshav Maharaj blocks this off the front foot.

Excellent effort from Kyle Jamieson in the deep! A short ball, on middle. Kyle Verreynne looks to pull but it goes off the top edge towards the fine leg region. Jamieson there, hops in front of the ropes, catches the ball but parries the ball back in play as the momentum was takinh him over the ropes. The batters take a single.
Short of a length, on off. Kyle Verreynne covers the line of the ball and blocks it.
Back of a length, on off. Kyle Verreynne blocks it onto the deck.
Henry follows it up with a length ball, around off. Kyle Verreynne keeps it out.

FOUR! Century for Kyle Verreynne! What a sensational knock this has been from the wicket-keeper batter. This innings can well prove out to be a difference between the two sides. He has taken his team to a commanding position now. Coming to the ball, it is on a length, on middle. Kyle Verreynne works it towards backward square leg for a boundary. Kyle Verreynne is pumped up and his team-mates are all standing in the dressing room applauding this fabulous effort.
A fullish delivery on off. Maharaj blocks it out. A bit of inswing there.
Back of a length, outside off. Kyle Verreynne cuts it to deep point for a single.
A length delivery, on off. Kyle Verreynne drives it nicely to mid off.
Back of a length, on off. Kyle Verreynne punches it to covers.
On a length, on middle. Kyle Verreynne works it towards backward square leg for a couple.
A full delivery on middle. Kyle Verreynne drives it to mid on.

FOUR! Maharaj gets off the mark with a boundary and a bit edgy this time. On a good length around off. Maharaj gets an outside edge as he looks to defend it and the ball goes through the gully region for a boundary.
Keshav Maharaj is the next man in.

OUT! CAUGHT! Kagiso Rabada holes out! Henry bangs it into the deck, around off. Kagiso Rabada flat-bats it towards Colin de Grandhomme at long on who takes a simple catch. End of a brilliant innings from Rabada! He has taken his team to a very formidable position here!
Commentary.Howout: c Colin de Grandhomme b Matt Henry

Commentary.Commentary: A length ball, on middle. Kagiso Rabada defends it out.
Good-length ball, jagging back in from off. Kyle Verreynne gets an inside edge behind the stumps and he tries to block it. A single taken.
Slightly shorter in length, on middle. Kyle Verreynne hops in his crease and blocks it.
A length ball, on off. Kyle Verreynne keeps it out.
A length ball, angling in from middle. Kyle Verreynne tickles it behind square on the leg side for a run.
Around off, blocked out.
FOUR! Nicely done! Good-length ball, just outside off. Kyle Verreynne stays back and carves it through covers for a boundary. He moves into the 90s now!
Full and on middle. Kyle Verreynne flicks it through mid-wicket and takes a couple of runs.
Leg bye! A slower ball, on a length, outside off. Kagiso Rabada shuffles across and looks to whip it away but misses. He gets hit on his pad and the batters take a leg bye.
Jamieson comes 'round the wicket and serves a length ball, on off. Kagiso Rabada blocks it onto the deck.
Kyle Jamieson (16-2-41-1) is back into the attack after an expensive last over from Tim Southee.
Back of a length, around off. Kyle Verreynne keeps it out.
Play and a miss! On a length and outside off. Kyle Verreynne stays back and looks to cut it late but he misses.
A length ball, angling in from off. Kyle Verreynne prods and tucks it towards mid-wicket.
Back of a length, on middle. Kagiso Rabada nudges it to the leg side and takes a single.
Short of a length, outsdie off. Kyle Verreynne hangs back and cuts it to deep point for a run.
FOUR! Kyle Verreynne joins the party now! Short and wide, outside off. Kyle Verreynne cuts it over point and collects a boundary.
SIX! AND AGAIN! Southee comes 'round the wicket and serves it on a length, around middle. Kagiso Rabada backs away and smashes it over long on to bag a maximum.
SIX! BANG! Rabada is having some fun out there! A length ball, on middle. Kagiso Rabada whacks it over deep mid-wicket for a biggie.
A full ball, outside off. Kagiso Rabada has a wild swing at it but he misses.
FOUR! STREAKY! 50-run partnership is up now between these two! A full ball, outside off. Rabada looks to slog but it goes off the outside edge through the slip cordon for a boundary.
Back of a length, around off. Kagiso Rabada hangs back and defends it with soft hands.
On a length, around middle. Kyle Verreynne tucks it wide of mid on and takes a run.
FOUR! This time a pull shot and runs are flowing now! Henry bangs this short on middle. Rabada is not backing away and pulls it to deep mid-wicket for a boundary now.
SIX! Ohh..Rabada is hurting New Zealand here! He backs away again  and Henry goes little short on middle. Rabada slaps it over long on for a biggie.
Back of a length, on middle. Rabada makes room and blocks it.
Goes full again, outside off. Rabada tires to drive it but misses.
Fuller delivery and outside off. Rabada leaves it alone.
On a length, on off. Kyle Verreynne dabs it to point for a single.
SIX! This time a maximum! A fuller delivery on middle. Rabada stays deep in his crease and tonks it over long on for a maximum.
FOUR! Rabada has come out with a mood to play some shots here. A length delivery on off. Rabada lifts this towards deep extra-cover for a boundary.
Another play and a miss! A good-length delivery, outside off. Rabada looks to drive but is beaten again.
A good-length delivery, outside off. Rabada goes pushing for it but gets beaten off the outside edge.
A fuller delivery on middle. Kyle Verreynne flicks it to mid-wicket for a single.
Back of a length, outside off. Kyle Verreynne punches it through covers for a couple.
This time over mid off. A length delivery on off. Rabada lifts this over mid off. It goes high in the air but falls away from the fielder running to catch it from the ring and gets another couple.
Nice shot but timing not perfect there. A length delivery on off. Rabada drives it over mid on off the inside half of his blade for a couple.
Goes full on middle and a hint of inswing again. Kyle Verreynne drives it inside half of his blade to mid on for a single.
A length delivery on middle. Kyle Verreynne blocks it out.
Almost a yorker this time, a low full toss in the end on middle. Kyle Verreynne drives it to mid on.
A fuller delivery on off. Kyle Verreynne drives it to mid on.
Beaten again! A fuller delivery outside off and shaping away. Rabada drives again away from his body and gets beaten.
This time Southee beats him! A good-length delivery around off. Rabada tries to drive it but the ball beats the outside edge of his blade.
A fullish delivery on off. Rabada drives it to mid off now.
A length delivery on off. Rabada drives it crisply to short cover this time.
FOUR! Lovely shot by Rabada! A fullish delivery on off and shaping into Rabada again. He drives this off the front foot past mid on for a boundary.
On a length and this first ball after Lunch comes back sharply into Rabada. He looks to defend but the ball hits him high on the pads.
We are back for the second session and so are the players on the field. Kyle Verreynne and Kagiso Rabada are at the crease. Tim Southee will start with the ball after the Lunch break!
... Day 4, Session 2 ...

New Zealand did have their moments in the first session with two outstanding catches from Tom Blundell and Will Young. Their bowlers weren't upto the mark and with the second new ball being taken just before Lunch, they must now make sure that they wrap the tail quickly. South Africa would be more than happy with the way things have gone so far for them. They did lose a couple of wickets but Kyle Verreynne has made sure that the scoreboard keeps ticking. All in all, it has been a great session for the Proteas and they will now be looking to stretch that lead even more post Lunch. Do join us for the second session that begins at 6.10 am IST (12.40 am GMT).

Right then, 92 runs scored in the first session with the loss of 2 wickets and it is safe to say, another session that has been dominated by South Africa. Kyle Verreynne is playing a gem of a knock for his side here. The tourists now lead by 303 runs and they are comfortably in the driver's seat. The Kiwis weren't at their best with the ball and they would be a bit disappointed as they would have hoped for more wickets in this session.

Review! Tom Latham has opted for a review as Kyle Verreynne has been struck on his pad. That looked quite high to the naked eye. Let's see what the Ball Tracker has to say. Yes, it confirms that the ball would have missed the sticks and gone over it.

NOT OUT! Another one that jags back in sharply. A good-length delivery that is pitching around off. Kyle Verreynne looks to defend but the ball nips back in and hits his pads. There is a huge appeal but the umpire is not interested. New Zealand decide to take the review! The replays roll in and the UltraEdge shows no bat involved. The Ball Tracker rolls and it shows that it is pitching outside off and the ball is missing the stumps as it is going over them. So New Zealand lose their review and the original decision stays. Kyle Verreynne will continue after Lunch. New Zealand are 232/7 at Lunch on Day 4.
This one nips back in sharply. Kyle Verreynne looks to defend this length delivery on off. He, however, gets the inside edge onto his pads.
Finally he goes fuller on off. Kyle Verreynne drives it through cover-point for a couple.
Back of a length, again. Kyle Verreynne cuts it to right of gully now.
Back of a length again, around off. Kyle Verreynne just chops it towards gully this time.
Back of a length, around off. Kyle Verreynne looks to cut but gets the inside half of his blade onto the turf.
Second new ball is now available. Will the Kiwis take it straightaway? Yes, they do! Matt Henry (18-5-47-1) comes back into the attack.
A fuller delivery on middle. Rabada works it to mid on now.

The lead is now 301! A length delivery around off. Rabada pushes forward to defend but the ball catches the outside edge of his blade and races towards the third man fence. The fielder cuts it off and the batters run couple.
On a length, on off. Rabada blocks it out.
A full toss this time and a bit high. It's a knuckle ball and Kyle Verreynne pulls it to deep square leg for a single.
FOUR! Boundary again. It has been a very good innings from Kyle Verreynne! A length delivery, outside off. Kyle Verreynne cuts it through backward point for a boundary.
FOUR! EDGY! Back of a length, outside off. Kyle Verreynne stays back and throws his bat at it. It takes the outside edge and flies past the second slip fielder for a boundary.
This one again, shapes away from Rabada. He leaves it alone.
This time fullish length, outside off. Rabada lets it go again.
A length delivery, outside off. Rabada leaves it alone.
This time, Colin de Grandhomme produces a peach! A good-length delivery around off. Rabada goes pushing for it but the ball seams away a bit and beats the outside edge of his blade.
Kagiso Rabada walks out to bat.

OUT! TAKEN! Ohh...what a catch! Will Young, you beauty! Produces a moment of brilliance to lift his team here! Absolutely fabulous stuff. A length delivery on middle. Jansen flicks this aerially towards deep mid-wicket. Young runs to his left and the ball is travelling away from him and it's even behind him. He, however, dives to his left and takes a one-handed stunner to ger rid of Jansen. His team-mates are thrilled and Marco Jansen is absolutely stunned after seeing that effort from Young. So two great ctaches from Kiwis this morning.
Commentary.Howout: c Will Young b Colin de Grandhomme

Commentary.Commentary: A length delivery on off. Jansen drives it back to the bowler.
Another delivery, on a length and around leg. Jansen works it towards backward square leg for a single.
A length delivery on middle and 123.5 kph. Kyle Verreynne works it to mid-wicket for a single.
On a length and around off. Jansen pushes it to deep point for a single.
Beaten this time! A good-length delivery and angling across the right-hander. Jansen looks to drive but misses.
A length delivery, on off. Jansen drives it to mid off.
A very full delivery outside off. Kyle Verreynne carves it to deep point for a single.
Back of a length, outside off. Kyle Verreynne stays back and punches it through the point region to collect a single.
On middle and fuller. Jansen works it to mid-wicket for a single.
FOUR! Boundary now for Jansen! Colin de Grandhomme drifts on the pads this time. Jansen flicks it towards backward square leg for a boundary.

Review! New Zealand have taken a review for Caught behind against Marco Jansen. The original decision is not out. The replays roll in and the UltraEdge shows no bat involved. So Marco Jansen will continue.

NOT OUT! Colin de Grandhomme drags his length back, outside off. Marco Jansen looks to cut but he misses. Colin de Grandhomme feels that there was a tickle on it and he convinces his skipper to take a review. The UltraEdge shows that there was no bat involved and New Zealand lose a review.
Edged but safe! A full ball, outside off. Marco Jansen looks for a booming drive but he gets an outside edge which falls short of the gully fielder.
Pitches it up, on off. Marco Jansen blocks it off the front foot.
Back of a length, on middle. Kyle Verreynne stands tall and blocks it.
A full ball, outside off. Kyle Verreynne drives but finds the fielder ar extra cover.
On a length, around off. Kyle Verreynne stays back to defend.
This one is on a length, around off. Kyle Verreynne defends it.
Fuller in length, on the pads. Kyle Verreynne flicks it through mid-wicket and bags a couple of runs.
On a length and angling across the batter. Kyle Verreynne blocks it.
A full ball, on middle. Marco Jansen leans and drives it to mid on.
Short of a length, around off. Marco Jansen lets it be.
Full and outside off. Marco Jansen drives it to the man at extra cover.
A yorker-length ball, on off. Marco Jansen digs it out.
On a length, outside off. Kyle Jamieson cuts it through point for a single.
Colin de Grandhomme starts wth a full ball, on off. Kyle Verreynne pushes back to the bowler.
Colin de Grandhomme is into the attack now, he replaces Kyle Jamieson. He has bowled just three overs so far in this innings.
Back of a length, well outside off. Marco Jansen lets it through to the keeper.
A length ball, on off. Marco Jansen defends it off the front foot.
BEATEN! A good-length ball, landing around off that shapes away a bit. Marco Jansen looks to defend but the ball beats his outside edge.
Shorter in length and angling across the batter. Kyle Verreynne guides it to deep point and rotates the strike.
Back of a length, outside off. Kyle Verreynne leaves it alone.
A full ball, around middle. Kyle Verreynne drives it to mid on,
Jamieson drags his length back, around off. Marco Jansen defends it solidly.
Fuller in length, outside off. Marco Jansen pushes it towards cover.
A length ball, around off. Marco Jansen blocks it.
BEATEN ALL ENDS UP! A length ball, just outside off that jags back in late. Marco Jansen looks to defend but the ball sneaks through his bat and pad.
Good-length delivery, around off. Marco Jansen rocks back to keep it out.
Hits the length hard, around off. Marco Jansen blocks it solidly.
Short of a length, well outside off. Marco Jansen does not bother playing at it. Kyle Jamieson oversteps again and the umpire signals no ball.
Good-length ball, around off. Kyle Verreynne hangs back to block it.
Back of a length, outside off. Kyle Verreynne does not offer a shot to this one.
Around off, blocked out.

DROPPED AND FOUR! Tom Blundell drops one now! Another ball, short and wide, outside off. Kyle Jamieson throws his bat at it. The ball catches the outside edge and flies just past the diving keeper for a boundary.
FOUR! Width on offer and Kyle Verreynne pounces on it! Short of a length, outside off. Kyle Verreynne cuts it past point and bags a boundary.
Back of a length, around off. Kyle Verreynne stays back and taps it to point.
Jamieson serves a short ball, aroud off. Marco Jansen lets it through to the keeper.

A bumper, around off. Marco Jansen ducks underneath.
Slightly fuller and on off. Marco Jansen pushes it towrads cover.
Back of a length, outside off. Marco Jansen punches it through covers for a brace.
On a length, around off. Marco Jansen gets behind the line of the ball to block it.
Back of a length, on off. Kyle Verreynne gets forward and defends it. A maiden over from Neil Wagner.
Good-length delivery, around off. Kyle Verreynne gets solid in his front foot defence.
On a length, around off and angling across the batter. Kyle Verreynne keeps it out.
Wagner serves it on a length, well outside off. Kyle Verreynne shoulders his arms at it.
On a length and angling across the batter. Kyle Verreynne leaves it alone.
Driven hard but straight to the fielder. Full and outside off. Kyle Verreynne drives but finds the fielder at extra cover.
Short of a length, just outside off. Marco Jansen gets low and lets it sail through to the keeper.
Good-length ball, outside off. Marco Jansen lets it be.

Back of a length, on off. Marco Jansen keeps it out.
Bangs it into the deck, outside off. Marco Jansen sways away from the line of the ball.
A length ball, angling in from middle. Kyle Verreynne tickles it to fine leg and brings up his FIFTY with a single. A good innings so far from South Africa's wicketkeeper.
Hits the deck hard, around off. Marco Jansen covers the line of the ball and defends it out.
Another delivery, on a length, around off. Jansen gets forward and blocks it.
Back of a length, around off. Marco Jansen prods and keeps it out.
A length ball, around middle. Marco Jansen defends it out.
A short ball, on middle. Marco Jansen ducks underneath.
Back of a length, outside off. Kyle Verreynne hangs back and cuts it to deep point for a single.

DRINKS! New Zealand have got the breakthrough just at the stroke of Drinks and they will now look to take the remaining wickets quickly. South Africa do have a good enough lead at the moment but they will be keen to stretch it even further. Marco Jansen walks out to bat.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Ohh...the extra ball has done the trick! This was not in the plan but Kyle Jamieson gets rid of well-set Mulder and breaks this dangerous partnership. A perfect delivery this by Kyle Jamieson. On a good length and around off. Mulder presses forward to defend it but the ball straightens after pitching and it catches the outisde edge of his blade. The ball goes towards right of Tom Blundell behind the stumps and Tom Blundell dives full length to take a one-handed stunner. A breakthrough for South Africa when the game was just drifting away from them.
Commentary.Howout: c Tom Blundell b Kyle Jamieson
